.TH SCREENSHOTS 1 "2026-03-01" "sway dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
screenshots \- screenshot capture, editing, and notification system for sway
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Screenshots functionality covers the full pipeline from capture to notification:
interactive region or output capture, annotation via
.BR swappy (1),
and two background daemons that fire desktop notifications when a screenshot is
saved to disk or copied to the clipboard.
.PP
Three scripts handle the distinct roles:
.TP
.B screenshot-frozen.sh
Used for region capture. Captures a full-screen PNG with
.BR grim (1),
displays it fullscreen with
.BR swayimg (1)
to produce a "frozen" visual, then launches
.BR slurp (1)
for interactive area selection. After selection, crops the chosen region out of
the frozen PNG using ImageMagick and writes the result to stdout. The caller
(the
.I $pipe_selection
variable) pipes this output directly into
.BR swappy (1).
.TP
.B screenshot-notify.sh
Daemon. Monitors
.I ~/Screenshots
(or
.IR $XDG_SCREENSHOTS_DIR )
using
.BR inotifywait (1).
When a PNG file is written (
.B close_write
event), fires a
.BR notify-send (1)
notification. Uses a lockfile and debounce logic to prevent duplicate
notifications. Managed by
.IR screenshot-notify.service .
.TP
.B screenshot-clipboard-notify.sh
Daemon. Uses
.B wl-paste --watch
to monitor the Wayland clipboard. When the clipboard contains a PNG image,
fires a
.BR notify-send (1)
notification. Uses a lockfile and debounce (500 ms) to prevent duplicates
when multiple clipboard events fire in quick succession. Managed by
.IR screenshot-clipboard-notify.service .
.SH KEYBINDINGS
Enter screenshot mode by pressing
.BR Print .
Inside the mode:
.TP
.B p
Pick region — launches
.I screenshot-frozen.sh
(frozen screen + slurp selection), pipes result into
.BR swappy (1).
.TP
.B o
Output — captures the current monitor with
.BR grimshot (1),
pipes into
.BR swappy (1).
.TP
.B Shift+p
Pick region and upload the PNG to x0.at; URL copied to clipboard and shown in a notification.
.TP
.B Shift+o
Output capture and upload to x0.at; URL copied to clipboard and shown in a notification.
.TP
.B Escape
Return to default mode without capturing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/screenshot-frozen.sh
Frozen-screen region capture; outputs cropped PNG to stdout.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/screenshot-notify.sh
Daemon: save-to-disk notification via
.BR inotifywait (1).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/screenshot-clipboard-notify.sh
Daemon: clipboard PNG notification via
.BR wl-paste (1)
--watch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/swappy/config
swappy editor configuration: save directory, filename format, panel defaults.
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/screenshot-notify.service
Systemd user unit for the save-notification daemon. Enabled for
.IR sway-session.target .
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/screenshot-clipboard-notify.service
Systemd user unit for the clipboard-notification daemon. Enabled for
.IR sway-session.target .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/screenshot
Sway mode configuration: defines
.I $mode_screenshot
and all keybindings, including the
.B Print
entry binding.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/01-definitions.conf
Defines
.IR $grimshot ,
.IR $pipe_output ,
.IR $pipe_selection ,
.IR $swappy ,
.IR $upload_pipe ,
and the composite
.I $screenshot_screen
/
.I $screenshot_selection
(with optional upload variants).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/autostart
Defines
.I $swappy_notify
and
.I $screenshot_clipboard_notify
variables (daemon restart commands).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/99-autostart-applications.conf
Calls
.I $swappy_notify
and
.I $screenshot_clipboard_notify
inside
.B exec_always
so both daemons restart on every sway reload.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/theme.conf
Defines the
.I $colorN
variables (e.g.\&
.IR $color5 ,
.IR $color7 ,
.IR $color10 )
referenced in the pango markup of
.IR $mode_screenshot .
The active theme is symlinked at runtime to
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
(generated \(em not tracked in git).
See
.BR palette-theming (1)
for the full theming system.
.SH PROGRAMS
.BR grim (1),
.BR slurp (1),
.BR swayimg (1),
.BR magick / convert
(ImageMagick),
.BR swappy (1),
.BR inotifywait (1),
.BR notify-send (1),
.BR wl-paste (1),
.BR wl-copy (1),
.BR curl (1)
(upload to x0.at)
.SH DAEMONS
Both notification daemons run as systemd user services under
.IR sway-session.target .
They are started (or restarted) every time sway reloads, via
.B exec_always
in
.IR 99-autostart-applications.conf .
.TP
.B screenshot-notify.service
Wraps
.IR screenshot-notify.sh .
The unit clears
.I /tmp/screenshot-notify.lock
via
.B ExecStartPre
before each start to prevent stale lockfile issues.
.TP
.B screenshot-clipboard-notify.service
Wraps
.IR screenshot-clipboard-notify.sh .
.SH FLOW
.SS Capture flow (region example)
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
User presses
.B Print
\[->] sway enters
.I $mode_screenshot
.IP \n+[step].
User presses
.B p
\[->] sway exits mode and executes
.I $screenshot_selection
.IP \n+[step].
.I $screenshot_selection
=
.I $pipe_selection
|
.I $swappy
: runs
.I screenshot-frozen.sh
piped into
.B swappy -f -
.IP \n+[step].
.I screenshot-frozen.sh
captures full screen \[->] displays with
.BR swayimg (1)
\[->] user draws selection with
.BR slurp (1)
.IP \n+[step].
Crops region from frozen PNG using ImageMagick \[->] writes PNG bytes to stdout
.IP \n+[step].
.BR swappy (1)
receives PNG on stdin, opens editor with annotation tools
.IP \n+[step].
User saves or copies; swappy exits
.SS Notification flow (save)
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
swappy saves PNG to
.I ~/Screenshots/
.IP \n+[step].
.I screenshot-notify.sh
detects
.B close_write
on the directory via
.BR inotifywait (1)
.IP \n+[step].
Debounce check (100 ms) prevents duplicate events
.IP \n+[step].
.BR notify-send (1)
fires "Screenshot saved" notification
.SS Notification flow (clipboard copy)
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
swappy copies PNG to Wayland clipboard
.IP \n+[step].
.B wl-paste --watch
in
.I screenshot-clipboard-notify.sh
fires callback script
.IP \n+[step].
Callback checks MIME type; if
.BR image/png ,
debounce check (500 ms) runs under
.BR flock (1)
.IP \n+[step].
.BR notify-send (1)
fires "Screenshot copied to clipboard" notification
.SH STORAGE
Screenshots are saved to
.I ~/Screenshots/
by default. Override by setting
.B XDG_SCREENSHOTS_DIR
in your environment before starting sway.
.PP
The swappy filename format is configured in
.I ~/.config/swappy/config
as
.BR save_filename_format=%Y-%m-%d-%H%M%S_swappy.png .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR grim (1),
.BR slurp (1),
.BR swappy (1),
.BR inotifywait (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
